radiographic_examinations.findings: Limited evaluation of the hepatic parenchyma; the gallbladder has been resected; a small fluid collection in the gallbladder fossa containing debris, approximately 5 cm.
Normal appearing liver with no evidence of intra or extrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation.
No osteolytic or blastic bone lesions; mild periosteal thickening along the fibula; diffuse soft tissue swelling with multiple phleboliths.
